  • Method Details

    • calculate

      double calculate(Feature<T> feature, FeatureCalculationInput<T> input) throws FeatureCalculationException
      Calculate the result of feature with a particular input.
      Parameters:
      feature - the feature to calculate.
      input - the input to calculate.
      Returns:
      the result of the calculation.
      Throws:
      FeatureCalculationException - if the feature cannot be successfully calculated.

    • calculate

      default ResultsVector calculate(FeatureList<T> features, FeatureCalculationInput<T> input) throws NamedFeatureCalculateException
      Calculates results for a list of features with a particular input, throwing an exception if a calculation fails.
      Parameters:
      features - list of features.
      input - the input to calculate.
      Returns:
      the results of the calculation for each respective feature, with Double.NaN (and the stored exception) if an error occurs.
      Throws:
      NamedFeatureCalculateException - if any feature cannot be successfully calculated.
